# Calendar data (RunningCalendar)

- **Single source of truth**: PostgreSQL on Supabase. Each fact belongs in one place. Do not duplicate the same information across columns (for example, do not store a separate display date when `sort_key` already holds the ISO date-time).
- **Normalized references**: Use slugs to reference `types`, `distances`, and `providers`; never repeat full labels or URLs where a slug FK suffices (except where the schema explicitly stores human-readable text, such as race `name` or city fields).
- **Schema changes**: If you need a new field, update `docs/data-model.md`, migrations on Supabase, `npm run validate-db`, loaders, and scrapers together.
